Ever since the days of Talleyrand, Chateau Haut Brion has been considered as one of the world’s greatest vine- yards. Its praises were sung in the diary of Samuel Pepys. Today, it is owned by the family of Clarence Dillon, and is often visited by his son, Hon. Douglas Dillon, the former Ambassador to France and Secretary of the Treasury.
